com.aylanetworks.aylasdk

类 AylaProperty<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.aylanetworks.aylasdk.AylaProperty<T>
  • 直接已知子类:
    AylaLocalProperty

    public class AylaProperty<T>
extends java.lang.Object
    An AylaProperty represents a "property" of an AylaDevice. Properties are used to control devices as well as obtain information about their current state. Properties are defined on the AylaService as part of the Template, and may not be created or destroyed. Aylaproperty is represented by a generic class, whose type is determined by the base_type of the property.

    Properties contain sets of AylaDatapoints, the latest of which is considered the property's "value". Therefore, changing the "value" of a property is done by creating an AylaDatapoint for the property.

    AylaProperties are obtained from AylaDevice objects by calling AylaDevice.getProperties() (to obtain the entire list of known properties), or AylaDevice.getProperty(String) to obtain a specific property by name.

    Properties may have AylaPropertyTriggers installed on them, which can be used to perform actions when a datapoint is created on the property that matches criteria defined by the AylaPropertyTrigger.

    The most common methods for AylaProperty include:

    • #createDatapoint(T, Map, Response.Listener, ErrorListener) to change the value of the property
    • getValue() to get the value of the latest datapoint for the property
    • fetchDatapoints(int, Date, Date, Response.Listener, ErrorListener) to fetch a set of datapoints from the cloud service for this property

      • getAckedAt

        public java.util.Date getAckedAt()
        Returns the time the latest acknowledgement was received from the device. Please note that this value may differ slightly based on whether the value was obtained directly from the device (LAN) or from either the Cloud Service (CLOUD) or datastream service (DSS). The source of the update may be found by calling getLastUpdateSource().
        返回:
        The timestamp of the acknowledgement of the datapoint from the device

      • getLastUpdateSource

        public AylaDevice.DataSource getLastUpdateSource()
        Returns the DataSource representing the service used to last update this property's status.
        返回:
        the DataSource last used to update this device's status. May be one of:
        • AylaDevice.DataSource.LAN last update came from device via LAN
        • AylaDevice.DataSource.DSS last update came from Device Stream Service
        • AylaDevice.DataSource.CLOUD last update came from Ayla Cloud Service

      • fetchDatapoints

        public AylaAPIRequest fetchDatapoints(int count,
                                      java.util.Date from,
                                      java.util.Date to,
                                      com.android.volley.Response.Listener<AylaDatapoint[]> successListener,
                                      ErrorListener errorListener)
        Fetches a collection of datapoints for this property from the server.
        参数:
        count - Number of datapoints to fetch. If zero, will fetch the maximum number of datapoints allowed in a single API call (MAX_DATAPOINT_COUNT).
        from - Date of earliest datapoint to fetch. May be null.
        to - Date of the latest datapoint to fetch. May be null.
        successListener - Listener to receive the array of datapoints
        errorListener - Listener to receive errors that may occur
        返回:
        the AylaAPIRequest used to fetch the datapoints
